like: The fact that biodiv1 explicitly shows the categories of search (e.g. "organism", "environmnt") makes it easier to organise and even come up with search ideas. biodiv2 is more straightforward to use, but it is up to the user to organise themselves, which is not an actual issue.
dislike:
In both cases, I wish that the results had a similar structure of attriutes when being presented. For example, many results did not have the "Labels" or "Description" attributes, and those could be explicitly marked as missing, because it would be easier to judge at a glance, which datasets I prefer, in relation to others. In the beggining of my search, I forgot about the "Labels" attribute, for example.
In biodiv1, the catgories can feel limiting, if the term I want to search for does not seem to fit in any of the boxes available.
